":-587},{"id":"recwKBkaALba6g0nG","ref":"Ezek.39.4","text":"Thou shalt fall upon the mountains of Israel, thou, and all thy bands, and the people that is with thee: I will give thee unto the ravenous birds of every sort, and to the beasts of the field to be devoured.","year":-587},{"id":"rec2bw63dv80ukrYy","ref":"Ezek.39.5","text":"Thou shalt fall upon the open field: for I have spoken it, saith the Lord GOD.","year":-587},{"id":"rechA2gOR0izpirQd","ref":"Ezek.39.6","text":"And I will send a fire on Magog, and among them that dwell carelessly in the isles: and they shall know that I am the LORD.","year":-587},{"id":"recKnWbk0qFA1EgHr","ref":"Ezek.39.7","text":"So will I make my holy name known in the midst of my people Israel; and I will not let them pollute my holy name any more: and the heathen shall know that I am the LORD, the Holy One in Israel.","year":-587},{"id":"recm04hTAJF64YOm8","ref":"Ezek.39.8","text":"Behold, it is come, and it is done, saith the Lord GOD; this is the day whereof I have spoken.","year":-587}]}
